property.name: description
property.value: The stars that surround the area while near [[Scissor Dancer]]s do not cover this path, indicating that it is walkable. This is hinted at by [[Seam]] when they say to "''walk where the stars don't shine''" after the [[party]] talks to them about [[Jevil]].

property.name: description
property.value: Interacting with this causes a switch to be discovered in it and be flipped, removing the tree blocking the right room. If [[Kris]] did not go around the center of the room before interacting with this, [[Ralsei]] will express amazement at them.

property.name: page
property.value: Block Tree

property.name: description
property.value: There are two paths at the top of each room. The path that [[Lancer]] goes on is incorrect, and the correct path is the opposite one.

property.name: description
property.value: There are three paths at the top of each room. The paths that [[Lancer]] and [[Susie]] go on are incorrect, and the correct path is the one neither of them go on.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] and [[Lancer]] introduce their team and team name, the latter being the same as what [[Kris]] chose earlier but with "''DARK''" as a prefix. After [[Ralsei]] asks what their evil plan will be, Susie says that they have only done their intro, and Lancer tells him to have some patience. They then say that they will work ceaselessly on their evil plan, after Ralsei says that he cannot wait to see what it will be.

object.name: Susie and Lancer leave with their blueprint

property.name: description
property.value: After [[Kris]] completes the puzzle, [[Susie]] and [[Lancer]] leave. She sarcastically thanks them for doing the puzzle for them. Lancer also says thanks due to them having trouble. They quickly come back and leave again to take the blueprint with them.

object.name: Create a machine to Thrash Your own Ass

property.name: description
property.value: [[Lancer]], disguised as a "''sweet young boy''," asks [[Kris]] and [[Ralsei]] to help him with something to impress [[Susie]]. Ralsei decides to help him out for the sake of his and Susie's friendship. The [[party]] can then choose what head, body, and shoes the Thrash Machine should have, along with the colors of each part. After the party finishes designing the Thrash Machine, Susie comes out from the bush, comments on the machine, and praises Lancer for tricking them into designing the machine for them, as long as it is not a duck.

property.name: page
property.value: Thrash Machine#Chapter 1

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ralsei]] is pleased that [[Susie]] finally found a place she fits in, and that she is also getting along with [[Lancer]]. When Susie rejoins the [[party]], she asks if Ralsei and Kris messed with her hideout. Ralsei questions if "hideout" is an overstatement, but Susie reaffirms she now owns it since she previously took a nap inside of it.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] and [[Lancer]] warn the [[party]] that they will likely get lost in the forest maze.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] questions [[Lancer]]'s whereabouts and is concerned for him being lost. [[Ralsei]] apologizes for worrying Susie, though she denies being worried and goes to look for Lancer. Ralsei hints that she does not know the correct path either.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ralsei]] sees the silhouette of the fake [[Thrash Machine]], though upon seeing it in full, he says it is not that good. [[Susie]] and [[Lancer]] then blow it up, saying that the [[party]]'s design sucked, so they blew it up. Instead of their plan, Susie states she and Lancer will fight the party and the losers will join the winner's side.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Lancer]] says that he has never been on such a large team before, though [[Ralsei]] is confused because he can command a legion of various guys. Lancer elaborates that [[King]] made them listen to him, so they do not actually like him. [[Susie]] tells Lancer that he does not need them anymore, as he has the [[party]].

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] comments that she is still hungry, as if nothing she has eaten in the [[Dark World]] matters. [[Ralsei]] offers to bake her a cake under the condition that she stops making fun of him, though she does not accept.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Lancer]] sees a [[Dark Candy|candy]] tree, though [[Susie]] cannot reach the last piece. To help her reach it, Lancer puts his hands on the floor and volunteers as a stool for her. Susie then gets the candy, but she gives it to Lancer upon learning that he has never had Dark Candy before.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] asks [[Lancer]] what the [[Dark Candy]] tastes like, and he says that it tastes like friendship. Upon inquiry as to what that tastes like, he says that it tastes like his teeth are disintegrating. After a short laugh, Susie remarks that that is not good, to which Lancer agrees. He then thanks her for being a good friend, but she is not sure what to say, so she just says "''you too''."

property.name: description
property.value: [[Lancer]] comments that walking next to the [[party]] feels nice, like he is doing something important. [[Ralsei]] explains that is because he is walking with [[Lightner]]s and [[Darkner]]s' purpose is to serve them as the only way they can feel fulfilled. Lancer feels worried upon learning this, as [[King|his dad]] wants to kill the Lightners. Ralsei asks if his dad seems happy, and Lancer is not sure.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] asks to stop talking about people's purpose and says that [[Lancer]] is probably just glad he ate a weird berry. He agrees, stating that he still has a boost from the juice. Susie elaborates by saying that she is a [[Lightner]] but still feels happy right now, though she denies feeling happy when [[Ralsei]] asks.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] amends her earlier statement that she is not happy by saying that maybe she is happy.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ralsei]] comments that the [[party]] can see [[Card Castle]]. [[Lancer]] points out that is where he and [[King|his dad]] live. Ralsei informs [[Susie]] that that is where the [[Dark Fountain]] is located, meaning she and [[Kris]] will be able to go home. She is relieved to hear this, though Lancer is uneasy.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Lancer]] questions if there is another way for [[Susie]] and [[Kris]] to return home, as the [[Dark Fountain]] is being guarded and he doe not want anyone to get hurt. He then says he needs to go. Susie asks when he will be back, and he replies that he will not be back. Afterwards, Lancer runs to the right. Susie follows him, and [[Ralsei]] follows her.

property.name: description
property.value: The [[party]] runs after [[Lancer]], though they are unsuccessful in reaching him before [[Card Castle]]'s doors close. [[Rudinn Ranger]]s surround them and knock out the party, sending them to the jail in Card Castle.

property.name: description
property.value: Only appears if the [[party]] talked to him earlier. Tells the party that he, along with [[Mr. Elegance]] and [[Mr. Society]], managed to fix the [[Warp Door]], and that it should be able to take them to and from here and the [[Field]] but that they will keep working on fixing it. Interacting again will have him question where the door may have come from.

property.name: page
property.value: Jigsaw Joe

property.name: description
property.value: If the [[party]] did not talk to [[Jigsaw Joe]], Mr. Elegance informs them that he and [[Mr. Society]] fixed the [[Warp Door]]; however, it might break because it was just the two of them. If the party talked to Jigsaw Joe, then he informs them that it should work fine because the three of them worked on it. Regardless, upon repeat interactions, he tells the party to not tell anyone that Mr. Society helped because he does not want the attention.

property.name: page
property.value: Mr. Elegance

property.name: description
property.value: Asks the [[party]] for help on getting something for [[Clover]]'s birthday and informs them that her only interests are sports, cute boys, and trees before giving up and saying that it will simply give her a card. Upon repeat interactions, it says that it might put money in the card before disregarding the idea due to needing the money.

properties.property: [[Ralsei]] inquires as to what Susie and [[Lancer]] are doing. Susie explains that they got bored and are having a snack, as they did not have a lot for breakfast. Ralsei further questions as to what the snack is and Lancer asks him to taste it himself. Ralsei offers for [[Kris]] to try it, with the following options available: * '''Make Ralsei try it:''' Ralsei finds that in the stump is a honeypot of salsa. Lancer says it is a snack from him to Ralsei, though Ralsei just pretends to eat it. * '''Decline:''' Susie tries it and assumes that the salsa is blood, before Lancer corrects her. * '''Try it:''' Kris finds that there is a honeypot of salsa inside the stump and eats some. All further interactions result in Susie saying that she is weakened by hunger, but that "you really shouldn't of" annoyed her. Ralsei corrects her wording, though Lancer and Susie disregard him.

[[Ralsei]] inquires as to what [[Susie]] and Lancer are doing. Susie explains that they got bored and are having a snack, as they did not have a lot for breakfast. Ralsei further questions as to what the snack is and Lancer asks him to taste it himself. Ralsei offers for [[Kris]] to try it, with the following options available: * '''Make Ralsei try it:''' Ralsei finds that in the stump is a honeypot of salsa. Lancer says it is a snack from him to Ralsei, though Ralsei just pretends to eat it. * '''Decline:''' Susie tries it and assumes that the salsa is blood, before Lancer corrects her. * '''Try it:''' Kris finds that there is a honeypot of salsa inside the stump and eats some. All further interactions result in Lancer asking if everyone has had enough and Susie replying "Constantly."

property.name: description
property.value: Lancer greets the [[party]] kindly, though [[Susie]] tells him to watch his language. He explains that she has been trying to get him to swear more.

property.name: description
property.value: Tells the [[party]] to open the treasure chest for a [[Dice Brace|Bracelet]], which will boost their defense. Upon further interaction, she says bracelets are her favorite.

property.name: description
property.value: Informs the [[party]] that [[King]] wants to eliminate [[Lightner]]s, but they and the other blocks disagreed, so all of them except the two here were arrested. Upon further interaction, states that [[Bow-Bow]] talks a lot.

property.name: description
property.value: Informs the [[party]] that [[Rouxls Kaard]] vandalized the puzzle, but she knows the answer and the first symbol is a heart. Upon further interaction, she repeats the clue.

property.name: description

property.name: description
property.value: Expresses frustration towards the puzzle due to none of the symbols being clubs.

property.name: description
property.value: Malius offers to fix the [[party]] or any [[item]]s they have. Fixing the party restores everyone's [[HP]]. Fixing items will repair the [[Broken Key]] pieces into the [[Door Key]] or repair the [[Broken Cake]] into the [[Top Cake]].

property.name: description
property.value: [[Susie]] and [[Lancer]] enjoy a purchased [[Hearts Donut]] together after receiving the funds from [[Kris]], who purchased a [[Lancer Cookie]] from them.

property.name: description
property.value: States that before [[King]] was in power, they ate leaves from the tree. In fact, they still do, as "''such is the way of the worm...''"

property.name: description
property.value: Only spawns in after ringing the bell on the other side of the room and coming back. He says that the birds are annoying him and that he is the "''original''" Starwalker.

property.name: description
property.value: Only appears here after entering the room from the right, ringing the bell on the other side of the room, and coming back. He says that the birds are annoying him and that he is the "''original''" Starwalker.

property.name: description
property.value: Expresses fear at the fact that [[Lancer]]'s made friends with a [[Lightner]] and says that someone should tell [[King]] immediately, although it will not be the one to tell him. Upon further interaction, it tells [[Kris]] to not look at it to do it.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ralsei]] asks how the [[Thrash Machine]] is going, and [[Susie]] states that they will work on it at the last minute, to which Ralsei suggests that they work on it sooner. Upon repeated interaction, Lancer comments that being a bad guy is relaxing, and Susie invites [[Kris]] to join if they are jealous. Ralsei states that Kris is not, but if they are, he would be willing to fan them.

property.name: description
property.value: Expresses annoyance that [[King]] makes them take care of [[Lancer]] and comments that, even though he is not a bad kid, the obligation means that nobody truly likes him. Upon subsequent interactions, it reflects that since nobody wanted to be his friend, he made friends with [[Susie]], who is rude, and that they should have been a better influence on him.

property.name: description
property.value: Asks the [[party]] to get [[Susie]] under control and make her stop forcing it to fan her, assuming that she and the party are together. Susie corrects it and states that they separated. Rudinn pleas for help, stating that it does not want to fan forever. Upon repeated interactions, it just repeats its pleas for help.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ralsei]] asks if Susie is ready to be good guy, but she says that being evil is more fun and that [[Lancer]] appreciates what she does. He then recounts how Susie ate a pinecone earlier and admires her for it. Upon further interactions, she asks Ralsei to stop blocking her "''reverse-tan''."

property.name: description
property.value: The first time the [[party]] ends up in this room, Lancer asks the party which way they are going next, though [[Ralsei]] tells him that they were following him, to which Lancer asks why because he does not know the correct path. Ralsei tells [[Kris]] to go where Lancer does not go. Upon repeated interaction, Lancer says that he was following the party but "''in reverse''." If the party comes in here another time, Ralsei reminds Kris to not follow Lancer.
